Stephanie Sims, I too, have a 13 year old daughter that thinks she and her best friend might be in love. There are many full out in the open gay and lesbian kids at her school. Many times it's difficult to figure out which ones are boys and girls. We live in a sheltered small town and in the heart of the Bible Belt, go to church, husband/her dad is a worship leader. Her best friend's parents were so distraught, they moved about a week ago. We are struggling to keep our daughter grounded. She still wears girly clothes, has long hair, wears makeup, and giggles around cute boys. I KNOW she is NOT gay! The open acceptance has caused our kids to be descensatized and confused. Our college (University of TN) has decided to add a bunch of unisex bathrooms. I'm ok with diversity, but this is going way too far!!!
